Xp never builds anything it can't be proud of, so we can deliver at any moment.

Rebuilding the plan. Think of it as changing the oil. You don't have to do it, but you'd be stupid not to.

Being held to someone else's estimates will lead to lack of commitment and falling morale. Don't do that.

Only at the end of an iteration do you really know where you are. So you never want to put that time off.

You can't manage what you can't measure.
